Program: Outlook
Title: Outlook Weekend: The Three Bears
Link: https://www.bbc.co.uk/programmes/w3cstzbf
Last Broadcast Date: Mon 30 Oct 2017
American Matt Dyer escaped death after a polar bear woke him up and dragged him away by his head. Russian pilot Sergey Ananov was aiming to be the first person to fly around the world in a light helicopter. He was forced to land in the Arctic Ocean where he discovered that he wasn't alone. Maggie and Andy Robin decided to buy a baby grizzly bear, he was named Hercules and became a big part of their family and an international star. Photo: Three bears Credit: Getty Images/VisualCommunications Show less